cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper proposes a technique to reduce the number of parameters and computation time in convolutional neural networks. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The use of Kronecker product also suggests that it may belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) category. Additionally, the experiments involve image recognition tasks, which are often associated with artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL) categories.
